properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets - THE ROCKS George St between Hickson Rd AND Lower Fort St
properties.otherAdvice:
Long term special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on George St in The Rocks to accommodate the weekly Rocks Markets.

Clearways will be in effect every weekend from 10pm Friday until 10pm Sunday on the eastern side of George St between Hickson Rd and Lower Fort St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs before parking as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

Road closures will also be in place on weekends for the markets from 4am Saturday until 10pm Sunday on sections on Argyle St, Artherden St, George St, Kendall Lane, Mill Lane and Playfair St.
properties.displayName: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - The Rocks Markets

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Wollongong education precinct - WOLLONGONG Princes Motorway, Memorial Drive at University of Wollongong
properties.adviceB: Plan your journey; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic management will be in place around University of Wollongong during morning peak periods to help ease congestion and queuing on the M1 Princes Motorway.

From 7:45am to 9:15am Monday to Friday:

  • M1 southbound traffic exiting at University Avenue will be diverted left, to make a u-turn at the eastern roundabout.
  • Traffic at Irvine Street will be diverted left, to the University Western Access route.
  • Motorists accessing the M1 Northbound onramp at Northfields Avenue via Irvine St may be diverted via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road if traffic is congested.

Motorists should allow extra travel time during morning peak and follow the instruction of traffic controllers.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Wollongong education precinct

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - SURRY HILLS Marlborough Street at Crown Street
properties.otherAdvice:
Permanent traffic changes will take effect from 10pm on Thursday 25 February.

  • Marlborough Street south will be closed to traffic at Devonshire Street, preventing access in all directions.       
  • Marlborough Street north will be restricted to a left in left out arrangement with Devonshire Street.       
  • The traffic lights at the Marlborough Street and Devonshire Street intersection will be removed.    
  • There will be no right hand turn both eastbound and westbound from Devonshire Street into Crown Street.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - KOOTINGAL New England Highway between Laurel Street AND Privet Street
properties.otherAdvice:
The intersections at Laurel, Pine, Oak and Privet streets will be closed until the end of May. Residents will be advised in advance if the intersections are required to remain closed beyond this time.   
The intersections of Wilson and Gill streets will be permanently closed and a short sealed service road will be built connecting these roads. Work to build the service road will start once the intersections are closed and is expected to take about one week to complete.

To accommodate rail replacement bus operations for Sydney Trains trackwork, special event clearways will be in place on the western side of York St between Margaret St and Barrack St from 2am Saturday 20 March until 2am Monday 22 March. 

Clearways are strict no parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.
properties.displayName: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS for rail replacement bus operations
